CONSOLIDATED CIGAR CORPORATION, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Joseph T. HIGGINS, as Collector, etc., et al., Defendants-Appellees. No. 278. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 10, 1936. Maass & Davidson, of New York City (David Weinstein and Monroe L. Friedman, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. John Davidson, of New York City, for appellees.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order reversed in open court.
